<section id="sect-Red_Hat_CloudForms-Scripting_Actions_in_CloudForms-Exporting_All_Datastore_Classes" remap="TID_15618">
	<title>Exporting All Datastore Classes</title>
	 <para>
		This procedure shows you how export datastore classes as an XML file.
	</para>
	 <procedure id="proc-Red_Hat_CloudForms-Scripting_Actions_in_CloudForms-Exporting_All_Datastore_Classes-To_Export_All_Datastore_Classes">
		<title>To Export All Datastore Classes</title>
		 <step>
			<para>
				Navigate to <menuchoice><guimenu>Automate</guimenu><guisubmenu>Import/Export</guisubmenu></menuchoice>.
			</para>

		</step>
		 <step>
			<para>
				Click 
				<inlinemediaobject>
					<imageobject>
						<imagedata fileref="images/2371.png" format="PNG" />
					</imageobject>

				</inlinemediaobject>
				 <guilabel>(Export all Datastore classes and instances to a file)</guilabel>.
			</para>

		</step>
		 <step>
			<para>
				Follow your browsers prompts to save the file.
			</para>

		</step>

	</procedure>
	 <formalpara id="form-Red_Hat_CloudForms-Scripting_Actions_in_CloudForms-Exporting_All_Datastore_Classes-Result">
		<title>Result:</title>
		 <para>
			The datastore is exported as a YAML file.
		</para>

	</formalpara>
</section>

